From 40cccc9fa708ef36c9bbea4b3aee818085894d54 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "Mr. Figueredo" <311303@dadeschools.net>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 03:08:26 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] Add advanced circle angle relationships and right
 triangle geometric mean: 4 new certified templates
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Closes more identified gaps: Chapter 10 section 10.5 (Angle
Relationships in Circles beyond the already-certified Inscribed Angle
Theorem — two-chords, exterior secant/tangent, and tangent-chord
angles were all uncovered) and Chapter 9 section 9.3 (Similar Right
Triangles / the geometric mean relationship for the altitude to the
hypotenuse).

New problem types (geometryProblemTypeRegistry.js v1.0.12 -> v1.0.13):
- circle_angle_two_chords
- circle_angle_exterior
- tangent_chord_angle
- right_triangle_altitude_geometric_mean

New certified templates (geometryTemplateRegistry.js v1.8.0 -> v1.9.0):
- circle_angle_two_chords_calculation: angle formed by two chords
  intersecting INSIDE a circle equals the average of the two
  intercepted arcs. Constructed answer-first (pick the angle, then
  split 2x that value into two arcs each capped under 180 for
  realism), verified this doesn't produce an oversized single arc
  after an initial Python check surfaced a 202-degree arc in an
  early draft.
- circle_angle_exterior_calculation: angle formed by two secants (or
  secant+tangent, or two tangents) meeting OUTSIDE a circle equals
  half the DIFFERENCE of the two intercepted arcs (far - near) —
  the companion theorem to the interior-chords case above, easy to
  confuse with it (this is exactly what the Distractor Engine's
  distractor for this template exploits, in the next commit).
- tangent_chord_angle_calculation: angle formed by a tangent and a
  chord at the point of tangency equals half the intercepted arc —
  mathematically the same halving relationship as the Inscribed
  Angle Theorem already certified, but a distinct named theorem in
  the curriculum, applied to a tangent-chord pair rather than two
  chords.
- right_triangle_altitude_geometric_mean_calculation: the altitude to
  the hypotenuse is the geometric mean of the two hypotenuse segments
  it creates (altitude = sqrt(seg1*seg2)); reuses the same
  divisor-search technique (integerDivisorsExcludingTrivial) already
  certified for intersecting_chords_missing_segment, guaranteeing an
  exact integer altitude.

New variable generator functions (geometryVariableGenerator.js
v1.10.0 -> v1.11.0), verified with 40 seeds x 4 templates (160 runs)
including independent mathematical re-derivation per run, plus
explicit range validation (arcs kept under 180 for the two-chords
template, far arc confirmed strictly greater than near arc for the
exterior template) — not just checking the formula holds, but that
the generated scenario is geometrically realistic.

Full regression: all 61 certified templates (57 previous + 4 new)
confirmed supported by the generator.

Still pending in this same feature: Solver, Distractor Engine, and
Prompt Renderer support for these 4 new templates (next commit).
